    <!-- ======================================================================
         RABBIT: New male subtype + pregnancy/weight + doe-input overrides.

         The overrides in this section are pre-release bork-fixes, NOT a
         modernisation pass. They address concrete gameplay bugs:
           - navMesh h=0.3, r=0.2 yields absurd derived weights: max=45,
             target=18. Real domestic rabbits: 2-5kg. Weight override
             corrects this.
           - The map's source XML uses sheep-scaled input rates (~16.5 L
             water/day, ~15 L food/day adult), which collapses doe Health
             to 0% within hours. Doe-input override mirrors the buck's
             rabbit-scale rates.
           - Witcombe defines no male variant; RABBIT_MALE creation here
             enables breeding.
           - Type-level pregnancy avg=4 / max=8 sets a sensible litter
             distribution.

         Modernisation runbook does NOT apply to RABBIT, by design:
           - The RLRM bundle defines no rabbit subtype, so there is no
             RL donor pattern to scale toward.
           - Base-game vanilla also defines no rabbit (Witcombe-defined
             species).
           - Cross-species mass-ratio scaling (e.g. rabbit_straw =
             0.055 x sheep_straw) is forbidden: numbers must come from a
             real source XML, not an invented ratio.
           - Adding rabbit output curves (manure / liquidManure / wool /
             meat) is a feature change, not a modernisation. Out of scope.

         Future agents: do not "modernise" this section by inventing
         scaled-from-cross-species values. If a future RLRM release adds
         authoritative rabbit data, re-evaluate at that point.
         ====================================================================== -->
    <animal type="RABBIT">
        <pregnancy average="4" max="8"/>

        <!-- Override: fix existing RABBIT (female) weights, breed, and consumption rates.
             Witcombe map's original input is sheep-scaled (16.5 L water/day, 15 L food/day adult)
